One study explains the ideology behind this belief stating that the adoption and personalization of Catholic values in ideology diminishes women’s ability to use their own autonomous decision-making and educates them to view premarital sex in a negative light where as the communist values in ideology, which were in possession before the merging of ideologies, let women focus on their careers first, thereby taught them to be liberal when it came to sex and the basic view was that of not viewing a woman as a sexual object. It is also claimed that abortion laws work against safe abortions, this being suggested by the young women who had started conducting self abortions from the age of 14 years simply as they were ignorant enough to think that the risk would be worth it. This proves the fact that women, especially in these developing countries, lack access to quality reproductive health services, and even more pointedly, information and referral systems to safe and legal abortions. Although doctors seem reluctant possibly for religious reasons, to instigate abortions, most doctors have admitted that they anonymously perform abortions but do not officially admit to it.

The most vulnerable groups that are prone to abortions include, heterosexual sex workers; ethnic and racial minorities; rural women and girls; young women and girls and adolescents under the age of 20. According to UN reports, about 70% of HIV infections in sub-Saharan Africa were young girls because of the shortage of information and a scarcity in reproductive health services and its allocation for young girls.
